1.title: Episode #17.1
1.plot: Newcomer Tim Medhurst and Christina Trevanion tour a wet south-west England in a MG Midget. Christina travels on a historic rescue boat, Tim tells the story of an unsung hero of aviation and spends his money on military memorabilia.

2.title: Episode #17.2
2.plot: Christina goes caving to learn about maturing cheddar cheese before setting her sights on a very old egg. Tim has a lesson in firefighting aboard a historic boat. An emu, a kangaroo and a frog go under the hammer in Exeter.

3.title: Episode #17.3
3.plot: Tim continues his tobacco habit with a Boer War pipe, Christina offers a sermon from behind a Victorian lectern. Touring Somerset and Devon, Tim scales a 500ft cliff while Christina climbs a wardrobe.

4.title: Episode #17.4
4.plot: After an encounter with some wild ponies in the New Forest, Christina turns farrier while Tim buys a horse. Will a George III commode help Christina? and will Tim's soggy bottom hinder him?

5.title: Episode #17.5
5.plot: In the final stretch Tim and Christina head through the Cotswolds and on to Wales. Tim rings some big bells and finally buys a coin. Christina visits a design museum and stocks up on silver and jewels.

6.title: Episode #17.6
6.plot: Charles Hanson and Margie Cooper begin a new road trip in the Scottish Highlands. Charles traces the family tree of a dog while Margie hears about a precursor to the NHS. At auction Charles's spoons go up against Margie's mirror.

imdb.title: Antiques Road Trip
plot: Two antiques experts compete against each other over five days buying antiques and selling them in five auctions. The programme is done in a light hearted fashion with all profits going to charity.
